LEGAL NOTICE
=============

rar-rs is a clean-room Rust implementation of the RAR5 archive format for
software conservancy and educational purposes, providing BSD-2-Clause licensed
`rar` and `unrar` command-line tools.

Clean-Room Implementation
--------------------------

The RAR5 LZSS+Huffman compression codec (src/codec/) was developed as a
clean-room implementation. The bitstream format was derived from analysis of
libarchive's archive_read_support_format_rar5.c by Grzegorz Antoniak (2018),
which is itself an independent BSD-2-Clause licensed implementation of a RAR5
decompressor. No proprietary RARLAB source code was used or referenced.

This project does not contain, link to, or derive from the proprietary unrar
source code distributed by RARLAB under its restrictive license. The archive
header and block structure implementation is based on the publicly documented
RAR5 format specification.

Scope and Limitations
----------------------

This software:

  - Does NOT supersede, replace, or replicate the full capabilities of the
    native RAR archiver produced by RARLAB (Alexander Roshal). The proprietary
    RAR encoder uses advanced techniques (including optimal parsing, context
    modelling, and PPMd) that this implementation does not attempt to reproduce.
    Compression ratios will vary; this implementation may produce larger output
    than the native tool in many real-world scenarios.

  - Is intended for software conservancy, interoperability, and educational use.
    It enables reading and writing of the RAR5 archive format without depending
    on proprietary binaries.

